description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an Advanced Mental Health Liaison Practitioner (Band 7) Team Lead Post to work for Lancashire and South Cumbria NHS Foundation Trust (LSCSFT) with the Mental Health Liaison Service (MHLT) in based at the Royal Lancaster Infirmary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be provide leadership and manage the day to day operations of the Liaison team who provide comprehensive assessments of people presenting with mental health difficulties at Lancaster Emergency Departments or on acute hospital wards at Lancaster Royal Infirmary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lancashire and South Cumbria NHS Foundation Trust (LSCFT) is looking for candidates with the following qualifications, skills and knowledge:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Nurse (Mental Health) with current NMC registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have at least 2 years’ experience at Band 6&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate evidence of Professional updating and development in the care of patients in an acute and community setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diploma in Professional Studies (Nursing) or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive Knowledge and experience of various approaches to mental health assessments for Adult &amp; Older Adult service users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience and knowledge of assessment of risk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Leadership skills with a key focus on performance of the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to develop strong partnership working with other key agencies such as the Acute Trust, Police, LCC, NWAS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates are expected to work closely with the Home Treatment Services and the third sector to develop and formulate care plans to support service users in community-based interventions as part of their role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications should demonstrate commitment to delivering LSCFT vision of high quality care, in the right place, at the right time, every time. Candidates should demonstrate that they are committed to LSCFT values of Integrity, Respect, Excellence, Accountability, Compassion and Teamwork.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LSCFT is committed to putting people who use our services are at the heart of everything that we do. Ensuring that people are motivated, engaged and proud of the services, they provide. Always being the best you can be.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note a job share can not be offered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameGail PorterJob titleService ManagerTelephone number01524 550582&lt;/p&gt;
